name: GAURAV C SAWANT
text: Look at voter turnout. Despite the heat & dust people queue up for hours to vote. Voting percentage remains v high. Institutions keep a hawk eye on political leaders. Media reports & debates actions of the govt & the opposition. Target the govt but spare the nation. #IndiaFirst

name: GAURAV C SAWANT
text: Consider the long & influential list of those who called the #BatlaHouse encounter fake, even before the probe was over. Academics, lawyers, influencers & the narrative constructed. Was it deliberately built ignoring facts on ground that @DelhiPolice repeatedly tried to give out?

name: GAURAV C SAWANT
text: The team carried out painstaking probe. CCTV camera images, car dealers, informers, mobile numbers. one mobile number was traced back to L18, Batla House. It was shared with central agencies & @DelhiPolice. Once Delhi module was busted after #BatlaHouseEncounter, Delhi was safer.

name: GAURAV C SAWANT
text: #IndianMujahideen terrorists had also planned serial blasts in #Surat. IEDs planted on trees & billboards to inflict head injuries. Fortunately the circuit was defective.100s of lives were saved. A @GujaratPolice officer had told me a special team was constituted to neutralise IM

name: GAURAV C SAWANT

text: Nathu La 1967 & Sumdorong Chu 1986 are honorable exceptions when India responded militarily & both times China retreated. But subsequently India didn't focus on building border infrastructure & strong forces to counter expansionist #China.Doklam 2017 & Ladakh 2020 are eye openers

name: GAURAV C SAWANT
text: Of course there is a military disparity. And it is a fact that China is both militarily & economically stronger. Yet Indian QPQ Ops forced an expansionist power to pull back. 'Salami slicing' of Indian territory has been on for decades. India in the past chose not to react to it.

name: GAURAV C SAWANT
text: A strong message shud go from every Indian. Govt & people. As far as possible, an effort can & should be made to replace #MadeinChina equipment with #MadeinTaiwan, #MadeinJapan & most important #MadeinIndia products. #AtmaNirbharBharat push a must by one & all to keep #IndiaFirst https://t.co/ZdqxUoThlV

name: GAURAV C SAWANT
text: China should never have been in power, telecom, railways sectors given the overt & covert hostile actions and it should be ejected. Better late than never. India must also consider undertaking QPQ action in cyber space. Balakot & Pangong are ample proof of India's strong resolve.

name: GAURAV C SAWANT
text: QUAD may not be a military alliance but is a mechanism to put expansionist forces on notice. Steps India takes are followed up by others. App ban may be followed by other more effective measures. On ground, military infrastructure development in border areas is being speeded up.

name: GAURAV C SAWANT
text: Has status quo ante been restored? No. But neither have Ops come to an end. India has made it clear to üá®üá≥ ties cannot improve if borders are not calm. If China wants economic ties to improve then restore status quo ante. Chinese App ban, selling hardware to Philippines imp signal

name: GAURAV C SAWANT
text: From #Surgicalstrike after #Uri to #Balakot air strikes after #Pulwama to #QPQ Ops both North & South of PangongTso on Aug 29-30 after Chinese moving to Finger 4 in Apr-May 2020, India's message is taking the battle to dominate the adversary on ground.This is a big mindset change

name: GAURAV C SAWANT
text: For decades infrastructure development was ignored along #LAC. Army brass insist past 5 years saw a massive boost to border infrastructure development. name: GAURAV C SAWANT
text: @Ambreenzaidi They are scary mam. The sound that precedes the avalanche and the haze. Just shows how insignificant we humans are in front of mother nature. & here after one avalanche this afternoon, the river's course was blocked & the river was flowing on the road. We were stranded for hours.

name: GAURAV C SAWANT
text: @sandythapar @BROindia You are right sir. And the usually gentle snow pierces the face like a thousand needles in thr hesvy winds at these altitudes. Impressed with the hard work put in by those tasked to keep #Zojila open through winters. @BROindia @nhidcl

name: GAURAV C SAWANT
text: @Dayalveersingh6 Kudos to the professional approach of @BROindia & @nhidcl in tackling the multiple avalanche hit pockets on the Sonamarg to Gumri road. Some of the dozers don't even have a weather shield, cover on top. Hats off to the dozer operators. Unsung heroes of the mountains.

name: GAURAV C SAWANT
text: @sandythapar Sir when the avalanche hit the road, only thing that came to mind was recover camera, Mike & dash to safety. Very impressed with the professionalism of @BROindia & #NHIDCL teams. Within minutes of info reaching them, they cleared the debris, attacking the problem from both sides.

name: GAURAV C SAWANT
text: Was trapped on an avalanche hit road. Some military vehicles on one side of the avalanche. Our vehicle in between & suddenly another snow slide in front. Mountains & mother nature show humans how small we in front of their might & then massive JCBs removed the debris in minutes. https://t.co/5a35Kjb32Y

name: GAURAV C SAWANT
text: With the #Zojila #Tigers at work. Heavy snowfall. Multiple avalanches. Minus 10 to minus 15 degrees temperature. But the teams are at it trying to clear the roads. One of the most challenging assignments. Reporting from #Zojila in Feb. No gentle snowflakes here. #IndiaFirst https://t.co/XVS4q5jqjY

text: So let's get out of this defeatist mindset what if China comes again. Let China think what will India do next, if China tries to misbehave again. The trouble is not yet over. It is a tricky situation. So stand firm with the forces who have checkmated China forcing it to pull back

name: GAURAV C SAWANT
text: China now knows the Indian mind. India will not buckle under pressure. India did not seek peace or resolution on China's terms. India stood firm. Took control over Kailash range to send out a stern message to China. This is a game two can play & India plays this game even better.

name: GAURAV C SAWANT
text:
Indian Army checkmated China at Kailash ranges & has other aces up its sleeve. China has realized India will no longer permit Chinese transgressions. 
Temp halt in patrolling is to calm the situation down.
India China stand off/tensions will continue either in Ladakh or elsewhere

2. We tried to patrol till our claim line Finger 8. There was resistance by PLA. 
3. PLA tried to patrol till Finger 4 own Tps went from 3 & stopped them.

text: We are determined to protect sovereignty & territorial integrity. Complete disengagement possible if Chinese honest about commitment during foreign minister's meet at Moscow.Ready to deal with any eventuality: @rajnathsingh in Parliament. House has faith in valour of armed forces

name: GAURAV C SAWANT
text: Sensitive situation on ground. Am convinced forces protecting borders. India working extensively on border infrastructure. Better logistical support to our forces & for better response on ground. Want peaceful resolution of issue. Met chinese defence minister in Moscow.

name: GAURAV C SAWANT
text: 29th Aug China again violated protocol. 1993 & 1996 agreement violated. India followed agreements. Thus face off. Violent conduct of Chinese forces violation of all agreement. Goghra KongkaLa PangongTso remain friction points. India has done counter deployment. Proud of our force

name: GAURAV C SAWANT
text:
China targeted our forces. Our forces responded with valour in difficult circumstances. Where calm was required it was shown where valour was required it was displayed. India wants peace at LAC. 3 principles
1. Peace
2. Don't change status quo
3. Follow laid down agreements...

name: GAURAV C SAWANT
text: April 2020 increase in chinese troop strength. May 2020 china interdiction of Galwan patrolling. Goghra & Pangongtso & KongkaLa. Indian forces timely response action. Both commanders met on June 6 2020 for disengagement process. Believe in LAC & no change in LAC. But June 15...

name: GAURAV C SAWANT
text: Peace & tranquility at LAC post 1988 relationship developed. 1993, 1996 agreement: keep less troops at LAC. Common understanding. 1990 2003 effort made but then China stopped. Overlap in perception at some places at LAC. Elaborate & time tested intelligence gathering mechanism:RM
